[1] Then I stood on the sand of the sea. And I saw a beast rising up out of the sea, having seven heads and ten horns, and on his horns ten crowns, and on his heads a blasphemous name. [2] Now the beast which I saw was like a leopard, his feet were like the  feet  of a bear, and his mouth like the mouth of a lion. The dragon gave him his power, his throne, and great authority. [3] And I saw one of his heads as if it had been mortally wounded, and his deadly wound was healed. And all the world marveled and followed the beast. [4] So they worshiped the dragon who gave authority to the beast; and they worshiped the beast, saying, “Who is like the beast? Who is able to make war with him?” [5] And he was given a mouth speaking great things and blasphemies, and he was given authority to continue for forty-two months. [6] Then he opened his mouth in blasphemy against God, to blaspheme His name, His tabernacle, and those who dwell in heaven. [7] It was granted to him to make war with the saints and to overcome them. And authority was given him over every tribe, tongue, and nation. [8] All who dwell on the earth will worship him, whose names have not been written in the Book of Life of the Lamb slain from the foundation of the world. [9] If anyone has an ear, let him hear. [10] He who leads into captivity shall go into captivity; he who kills with the sword must be killed with the sword. Here is the patience and the faith of the saints.  [11] Then I saw another beast coming up out of the earth, and he had two horns like a lamb and spoke like a dragon. [12] And he exercises all the authority of the first beast in his presence, and causes the earth and those who dwell in it to worship the first beast, whose deadly wound was healed. [13] He performs great signs, so that he even makes fire come down from heaven on the earth in the sight of men. [14] And he deceives those who dwell on the earth by those signs which he was granted to do in the sight of the beast, telling those who dwell on the earth to make an image to the beast who was wounded by the sword and lived. [15] He was granted power to give breath to the image of the beast, that the image of the beast should both speak and cause as many as would not worship the image of the beast to be killed. [16] He causes all, both small and great, rich and poor, free and slave, to receive a mark on their right hand or on their foreheads, [17] and that no one may buy or sell except one who has the mark or the name of the beast, or the number of his name. [18] Here is wisdom. Let him who has understanding calculate the number of the beast, for it is the number of a man: His number is 666.

How to Achieve Monotheism and the Meaning of Polytheism and Injustice
Question:

What are the things that achieve monotheism? And what is the meaning of polytheism and injustice
Answer:

Monotheism is achieved by sincerely worshipping Allah - the Almighty and Exalted - and believing that He is worthy of worship, and that He is One in His Lordship, and One in His Divinity, and One in His Names and Attributes, and that He, glory be to Him, has no likeness, and no partner, neither in His actions, nor in His words, nor in His attributes, and that He alone is worthy of worship, and no one else deserves it  with belief in everything that Allah and His Messenger have informed us of, and permitting what Allah and His Messenger have permitted, and forbidding what Allah and His Messenger have forbidden; this is monotheism, this is faith, and the guidance by which the servant becomes a Muslim.

 Sheikh: Repeat the question.

Question: What are the things that achieve monotheism, and what is the meaning of polytheism and injustice?

Answer: As for the meaning of polytheism and injustice, polytheism means: making a partner for Allah in worship whom he calls upon along with Allah, such as a saint, a prophet, a tree, or an idol, whom he calls upon along with Allah, seeks help from along with Allah, makes vows to him, etc., this is the partner.

It is also applied to minor polytheism, such as the one who worships Allah for the sake of a dirham or a dinar, wretched is the slave of the dinar, wretched is the slave of the dirham, and thus hypocrisy is a type of minor polytheism, and it is also applied to everyone who disbelieves and is called a polytheist, everyone who disbelieves in Allah by denying what Allah has permitted, or denying what Allah has forbidden, or cursing Allah and His Messenger is called a disbeliever.

He is called a polytheist;  Because by doing this he obeyed his desires, and associated his desires with God in worship, and obeyed the commands of desires and Satan, and became a disbeliever for denying what God has made obligatory, such as denying the obligation of prayer, or denying the obligation of fasting Ramadan when able, or denying what God has permitted of camels, sheep, and cows, or permissible grains of wheat, barley, and the like, or insulting God, or insulting the Messenger of God, or mocking the religion of God, or the like. These are types of disbelief and polytheism.

And mention, [O Muhammad], in the Book [the story of] Mary, when she withdrew from her family to a place toward the east.

She said, "Indeed, I seek refuge in the Most Merciful from you, [so leave me], if you should be fearing of Allah ."

He said, "I am only the messenger of your Lord to give you [news of] a pure boy."

She said, "How can I have a boy while no man has touched me and I have not been unchaste?"
He said, "Thus [it will be]; your Lord says, 'It is easy for Me, and We will make him a sign to the people and a mercy from Us. And it is a matter [already] decreed.' "
So she conceived him, and she withdrew with him to a remote place

And the pains of childbirth drove her to the trunk of a palm tree. She said, "Oh, I wish I had died before this and was in oblivion, forgotten."

But he called her from below her, "Do not grieve; your Lord has provided beneath you a stream

And shake toward you the trunk of the palm tree; it will drop upon you ripe, fresh dates.
So eat and drink and be contented. And if you see from among humanity anyone, say, 'Indeed, I have vowed to the Most Merciful abstention, so I will not speak today to [any] man

Then she brought him to her people, carrying him. They said, "O Mary, you have certainly done a thing unprecedented.

So she pointed to him. They said, "How can we speak to one who is in the cradle a child?"
[Jesus] said, "Indeed, I am the servant of Allah . He has given me the Scripture and made me a prophet

And He has made me blessed wherever I am and has enjoined upon me prayer and zakah as long as I remain alive

And [made me] dutiful to my mother, and He has not made me a wretched tyrant.

And peace is on me the day I was born and the day I will die and the day I am raised alive."

That is Jesus, the son of Mary - the word of truth about which they are in dispute.
It is not [befitting] for Allah to take a son; exalted is He! When He decrees an affair, He only says to it, "Be," and it is.
[Jesus said], "And indeed, Allah is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him. That is a straight path."

Perhaps you reject my analysis? Again, it doesn’t matter. And yet, I know of no one who could successfully disprove my conclusion that there is something deeply mysterious, hideous and seemingly indestructible within the ego and the intellect that unceasingly subverts our attempts to reach the light. Indeed, this is the corner stone of most of our religions and ideologies: the struggle to deny its presence or at least to defend ourselves as best we can. Having lost hope in ever returning to the source of everything, the average person finds solace in their selfishness.

Our age of technology further increases the risks to humankind and to our planet, in the sense it compels us to believe in a culture of entitlement. One only needs to study the culture we have created to understand its effect. The main theme appears to be that we are entitled to blissful happiness and endless options , that we are invincible and that, with the help of AI and technology, we each are destined to become a Homo Deus. And the bywords of our time show our obsession with greed, money, power, control, speed, productivity, efficiency, limitless growth and change, having myriad connections and options, and so on. 

This same culture teaches us that nearly anything is permissible in our search for self-fulfillment, that we are entitled to think, to say, to write, to do, to believe in anything, at virtually any cost. It relieves us of the responsibility for clarity, balance, tolerance, fairness, kindness and a myriad of other qualities we associate with the light.

For me though, it is a barren world that has no heart, no soul, no joy. Perhaps the biggest hoax that has ever been foisted upon us.

And yet, it might be that suffering and struggle is all there is? Ofttimes, I feel I will break in two, vomit, pass out or something when the memory of what people do and have done visits me. Words and actions I would never in a million years do onto others. Ah, but to suffer well, having faith that enlightenment will eventually come my way, finding something that is sustainable, not the vain distractions and short-lived illumination people shop for each day.

Surely, the most difficult undertaking in life is to side-step all that the world has lined up for us and to make a better way. In trying to do this, I practice “controlled folly”: first knowing that my acts are useless but nonetheless proceeding as if I didn’t know it. It often brings unexpected blessings that cannot be measured in a material sense. The antithesis of the “why bother mentality”. Admittedly, it is also a path fraught with danger as character assassins abound in the world. This is why I have chosen to write under a nom de plume. I have nothing to hide but, since I am only a vulnerable human being, it would be most foolish to leave myself open to attack.

Seems to me that, the more cobwebs one has on their TV, computer, phone and so on, the better their perception. We are always given the choice between becoming social chameleons, concealing our motives behind smoke and mirrors; or choosing a path of consistency and unwavering commitment to kindness and truth. Sadly, most people appear to have chosen the former, although they would lead you to believe otherwise.

In conclusion, the thrust of my life is to try my best to become a citizen of the world; not belonging to any tribe, nation or creed.

Here are some concerns regarding Donald Trump’s stance on women’s rights:

Reproductive Rights: Supported policies that restrict access to abortion, including appointing Supreme Court justices who overturned Roe v. Wade, limiting reproductive freedom in many states.

Healthcare Impact on Women: Tried to dismantle the Affordable Care Act, which covers essential women’s health services like maternity care, preventive screenings, and contraception.

Equal Pay and Workplace Rights: Limited focus on addressing the gender pay gap and protections for women in the workplace, affecting economic equality.

Handling of Sexual Harassment Allegations: Faced multiple allegations of sexual misconduct, raising questions about his stance on workplace respect and the importance of addressing sexual harassment.

Family Leave Policies: Limited federal action to expand paid family leave, which disproportionately affects women balancing work and family responsibilities.

Violence Against Women Act (VAWA): VAWA was temporarily stalled during his term, affecting funding and resources for victims of domestic violence.




On education, here are additional reasons why Trump may not have been the best fit:

Reduced Funding for Public Schools: Proposed cuts to federal education funding, which impacts resources for public schools, especially in lower-income areas.

Support for School Privatization: Pushed for school choice and voucher programs, potentially diverting funds from public schools to private institutions.

Student Loan Policies: Limited support for comprehensive student loan forgiveness and relief, leaving many graduates struggling with debt.

Cuts to Special Education: Reduced funding for programs supporting students with disabilities, affecting equitable access to quality education.

Less Focus on Diversity and Inclusion Initiatives: Limited emphasis on diversity training and inclusive curriculums, which are essential for fostering understanding and representation in schools.




Donald Trump's education policies have been a subject of debate, with several key aspects drawing criticism:

Proposed Elimination of the Department of Education: Trump has expressed intentions to abolish the U.S. Department of Education, aiming to reduce federal oversight in education. Critics argue this could lead to inconsistencies in educational standards and diminish support for disadvantaged students. 
THE WEEK

Promotion of School Choice and Vouchers: His advocacy for school choice includes redirecting funds to private and charter schools through voucher programs. Opponents contend this approach may divert essential resources from public schools, potentially widening educational disparities. 
US NEWS

Stance on Critical Race Theory and Gender Education: Trump has proposed banning the teaching of Critical Race Theory and certain gender-related topics in schools. Detractors believe such measures could limit comprehensive education on important social issues and suppress academic freedom. 
PBS

Impact on Higher Education: His policies have included efforts to reduce funding for higher education institutions and roll back regulations aimed at protecting students from predatory lending practices. These actions have raised concerns about accessibility and affordability of higher education. 
SAVING FOR COLLEGE

These points highlight the contentious nature of Trump's education policies and their potential implications for the U.S. education system.






Here are a few additional economic concerns regarding Trump’s presidency:

Weakened Small Businesses: Many small businesses faced higher costs due to tariffs and were heavily impacted by the pandemic, with limited support in relief programs that often favored larger corporations.

Healthcare Costs: Efforts to dismantle the Affordable Care Act without a viable replacement plan created uncertainty around healthcare costs, which can heavily affect personal and national economic stability.

Environmental Rollbacks Affecting Green Jobs: His administration rolled back environmental regulations, which critics argue stifled potential growth in green energy jobs and renewable industries, key sectors for future economic resilience.

Focus on Fossil Fuels Over Renewables: Support for coal and oil limited investment in renewable energy, leaving the U.S. behind other countries in green technology innovation and job creation.

Record National Debt Increase: Despite economic growth claims, the national debt rose significantly, partly due to tax cuts and stimulus packages without corresponding revenue generation, putting long-term pressure on the economy.

Policies that focus on modern infrastructure, sustainable energy, and small business support can drive healthier, more balanced economic growth over time.




Trade Wars and Tariffs: His trade policies, particularly with China, led to tariffs that increased costs for American consumers and hurt certain industries like agriculture and manufacturing.

Tax Cuts Favoring the Wealthy: The 2017 tax reform primarily benefited corporations and high-income individuals, leading to a significant increase in the national debt without equivalent economic growth for working- and middle-class families.

Inconsistent Economic Growth: While the economy initially grew under his administration, growth slowed even before the pandemic due to factors like rising debt and minimal wage increases for average workers.

Minimal Focus on Infrastructure: Despite promises to revitalize infrastructure, meaningful investments were limited, missing an opportunity for job creation and economic stimulus.

Response to COVID-19’s Economic Impact: His handling of the pandemic left many businesses and workers without adequate support, leading to a slower recovery and leaving certain sectors struggling.

Solution
The Safest Form of Money

What is the safest form of money? Through the century’s the people have been told gold is the safest form of money, but today in the 2020’s the Reserve Bank (RBNZ) says Central Bank Digital Currency (CBDC) “backed by Government” is the safest form of money. Why and safest for who?

Currently when Government over spends revenues, it funds the deficit by selling Bonds for liquidity created out of thin air by the Reserve Bank. The Bond Owners are paid yield (interest) on this debt from tax revenues and if not repaid are paid yield from future taxes. The economy is burdened if government debt is never repaid.

This system is already backed by the Government so you can understand why real taxpayers want the Government to be accountable, avoid waste at all costs and lower taxation if possible. But real taxpayers face the problem of too many drawing incomes from the taxes they pay from their productivity leaving not enough to build a hospital, fix roads, schools, bridges, water supplies etc. When a crisis comes along like the 2009 American Bank Bailout, 2010/11 Christchurch earthquakes, 2016 Kaikoura earthquake, 2020 Covid-19 pandemic and the 2023 Gabriella cyclone, Government expands the National Debt with no consideration to Gross Domestic Product (GDP) and possible tax revenues. Our government is guilty of borrowing currency to pay Bond Owners.

Now at a time when Dunedin needs a new hospital, Infrastructure Minister Chris Bishop says there is no Magic Money Tree (MMT) to pay for a new hospital. Bishop conveniently forgot the Reserve Bank used Modern Monetary Theory (MMT) after Covid to provide private banks and financial institutions with $55 billion dollars in 2021 and 2022 which stimulated the growth of private debt (inflationary) in the act of lending. 

To consider and define the “Safest Form of Money” it must be looked at from both public and private aspects. Modern Monetary Theory is a debt-based model creating all new currency as debt. This model suits the private sector as long as banks are given reserve constraints (deposits versus lending) to minimize credit creation in the act of lending to guarantee deposits and minimise inflation.

The Magic Money Tree is a debt-free model suited to Government in times of overspending. This model allows an authority like the RBNZ to create new debt-free currency for government to fund crises like bank failures, earthquakes, pandemics, cyclones and infrastructure requirements when the economy has not been taxed enough to pay for it. This means the government would no longer have to rely on banks (Bond Owners) for liquidity. Spent into the economy at zero interest, restricts inflation.

So, the promotion of CBDC as the safest form of money is a parasitic collaboration between the RBNZ and the Government who don’t care about real taxpayers.

The man America's elites couldn't contain, corrupt or clamp in irons has beaten all expectations and elite efforts to return to the pinnacle of U.S. power. What will he do with that power this time?

The ogre so many among the wannabe intellectual, arty, academic, liberal and student circles love to hate, is back, brought back by the working class who those first mentioned look down upon as second-rate citizens. Those who conceive themselves to be of higher class, entitled to make the rules for all others have received a mighty shock. They believed they were in an unassailable position to perpetually govern those they regard as rather ‘ignorant’ and uncouth who they think were in fact born to serve them while knowing their place. They believed their rightful role was to govern, to discipline, control and punish those beneath them, keeping them from straying. This was the role envisioned by the so-called great and good for themselves, the intellectuals, academics and all the other high-flown and entitled liberal elites and they expected all lesser mortals to be content with this, for them convenient, status quo.

The ‘great unwashed’ horde were supposed to be quiet and consume the rightful edits, narratives and agendas from those who ‘know better’, to accept their wars, to fight their wars when necessary and to applaud their wars through the vehicle of legacy news media. All that is now totally undermined with the rise of those ‘Unwashed’ hordes, adamant they will be hears and that their loud-mouthed and aggressive mouthpiece will be their agent of revolution, tearing apart that entitled and conceited liberal consensus. We won’t support your wars anymore and less and less of the poorer in this society will fight them either! At least for four years. The new and by the liberal class unexpected, unwanted and EXTREMELY unwelcome new Trump years.

Though Trump will be in office, will he be in power? Will he this time deliver on his promises? Will that swamp that he totally failed to drain and which remains as bog-ridden as ever? Will he once again be overwhelmed by ‘The Blob’, the permanent residents of the U.S. deep state who love nothing more than to see the USA at war? Will he TRULY engage Russia this time round or will he once again only APPEAR to do so while figuratively applying the knife to Russia’s back as he did last time? In 2016 he overrode Obama’s decision to forbid the Kiev regime lethal weaponry and without any doubt caused the deaths of a great many Russians who would ot have died otherwise, in doing so. Will his instinct to do what is best for HIM override all other priorities? Will his instinct to ‘MAKE TRUMP GREAT AGAIN’ blind him to what might make the world once again more peaceful?

Clearly Trump will embark once again on an expanded economic war against China. In doing so he will attempt what he recently claimed he would do, tear Russia and China apart. Can there be any doubt that his warm words toward Vladimir Putin and Russia will be seen to be mere semantic shoe-shuffling when compared to his dedication to weakening and splitting those two allies apart? Trump may think he is amazing and has the power to effect great change but we must hope he concentrates on the enormous woes of his own country before trying to inflict them on others, namely on the BRICS nations and specifically upon Russia and China. On Ukraine he talks big, but what can he deliver? It must be strongly suspected that his campaign trail rhetoric, designed merely to strike a powerful pose will find the actuality quite impenetrable and intractable. No easy solution will come from some simplistic, unrealistic and woefully naive banging of Russian and Ukrainian heads together. Neither will threats work, especially not against Russia. Of all bets on Ukraine, telling Zelensky that the U.S. cupboard is now bare as far as he is concerned is the very best of them. No more handouts. Tell the Ukrainian beggars they can now go wanting, see what the paupers of Europe can offer, or better still, get the best deal you can from Russia that it is still willing to offer.

He’s back. He appears stronger than ever. But will a newfound wisdom and humility be seen due to his years in the political wilderness. Will humiliation have taught him some of that vital ingredient, the humility that can come from eating the worst of crow? We have to hope so, because bravado and mouthing off won’t cut it any more if it ever did. And asking neocons to come protect you won’t either. The stupidity of that first term in taking on ideological monsters such as John Bolton, Mike Pompeo and their ilk was about as wrongheaded as it gets. With this second chance there is at least the merest possibility that truly great things can be achieved. They won’t be achieved however by setting the USA against the BRICS and the idea of a multipolar world however. Take that avenue and you walk down a cul-de-sac Donald, a road to the various wars, economic or otherwise, that the entire planet is thoroughly sick of. Beware that pugilistic stance you love so much. In some humility, walk on and see what true good you can do… for ALL of us.

CONGRATULATORY MESSAGE TO DONALD TRUMP

Dear President-Elect Donald Trump,

I am thrilled to be among the first to extend my warmest congratulations to you on your triumphant victory in the US presidential election. Your win is not only a testament to the trust and confidence of the American people, but also a manifestation of the divine favor and blessing of Almighty God.

As I reflect on your campaign, I am reminded of your courageous and inspiring speech, in which you boldly declared, "I believe God created Male and Female each with special Purpose." Those words resonated deeply with many, and I firmly believe that they drew God's favor upon you. Your unwavering commitment to the principles of faith, family, and freedom has earned you a special place in the hearts of people all over the world.

Your victory is not just a political achievement, but a divine mission to protect and preserve the human race, particularly the human seed, which is the foundation of our existence. I firmly believe that God has entrusted you with a sacred responsibility to fulfill His purpose on earth, and I pray that you will remain faithful to this calling.

As a representative of the low-profile community, I am honored to join the chorus of congratulations pouring in from around the world. I would also like to extend my congratulations to Mr. Elon Musk, a visionary leader who has been instrumental in shaping the future of humanity.

May I remind you, Mr. President-Elect, that your victory is not a personal achievement, but a sacred responsibility to serve the people and fulfill the will of God. I urge you to remain humble, steadfast, and committed to the principles that have guided you thus far. May God's wisdom, guidance, and protection be your constant companions as you embark on this historic journey.

Once again, I offer my heartfelt congratulations to you, Mr. President-Elect Donald Trump, and pray that you will continue to be a beacon of hope and inspiration to the world.

May God bless you, Mr. President-Elect, and may God bless America!

Making a case for Ukraine to develop a nuclear weapon by January 6, 2025, in response to a potential loss of U.S. funding, would likely revolve around a few key strategic considerations. This would involve analyzing Ukraine’s geopolitical needs, its capacity to act independently, and the implications for its national security. Here’s a possible rationale for Ukraine pursuing such a deterrent:

	1.	Deterrence Against Russian Aggression: Ukraine has faced ongoing conflict with Russia since 2014, with the war intensifying in 2022. Without U.S. funding, Ukraine could find itself more vulnerable against a significantly larger and more militarized adversary. A nuclear deterrent could provide Ukraine with a powerful tool to discourage further Russian advances or threats to its sovereignty. The knowledge that Ukraine has a nuclear weapon might change Russia’s calculus regarding any continued aggression.
	2.	A Response to Security Guarantees Lost: In 1994, Ukraine gave up its nuclear arsenal in exchange for security assurances under the Budapest Memorandum, with the U.S., U.K., and Russia pledging to respect Ukraine’s borders. However, Russia’s 2014 annexation of Crimea and the 2022 invasion indicate that these guarantees have not held firm. Without robust U.S. support, Ukraine might feel compelled to take its security into its own hands, potentially believing a nuclear deterrent is the only realistic way to ensure its sovereignty is respected.
	3.	Self-Defense in a Potentially Isolated Position: If U.S. funding and aid significantly decrease or end, Ukraine could face isolation from its strongest allies. This would leave it without the economic and military backing that has sustained its defenses. A nuclear weapon could compensate for this loss, providing Ukraine with a means of self-defense that does not rely on outside intervention or support.
	4.	Possession of Necessary Resources: Ukraine retains substantial nuclear expertise, having inherited the Soviet Union’s nuclear infrastructure and research facilities. It also has access to nuclear materials through its energy sector, and its missile technology could be adapted for nuclear delivery, giving it the technical foundation to potentially develop a nuclear weapon quickly. Ukraine has well-regarded scientists and an advanced technological base, suggesting that the project could be completed relatively efficiently if fully prioritized.
	5.	Geopolitical Leverage: Possessing a nuclear weapon could enhance Ukraine’s leverage in any future peace negotiations or in securing stronger international support. Knowing Ukraine could escalate to nuclear capabilities might encourage other nations to provide renewed security guarantees, even without direct U.S. involvement. It would add weight to Ukraine’s diplomatic efforts and could serve as a counterbalance to other regional powers.
	6.	Regional Power Balance: Other neighboring countries, such as Poland or the Baltic states, may view a Ukrainian nuclear weapon as a stabilizing factor in the region. Even if controversial, a nuclear-armed Ukraine could contribute to a balance of power, preventing further Russian aggression and potentially creating a buffer state that discourages escalation into other regions of Eastern Europe.

While there are significant risks, including potential backlash from the international community and diplomatic isolation, Ukraine might calculate that a nuclear deterrent is its best option for survival without U.S. support. The world would likely respond with a mix of diplomatic pressure and caution, but the perception of Ukraine as a nuclear power could effectively deter large-scale aggression. This path, though fraught, might appear as a last-resort solution for a nation facing existential threats with fewer external resources.

Chairman of the Southern African Development Community (SADC)


Dear Mr. Trump,
On behalf of the Southern African Development Community (SADC), it is with great pleasure that I extend our heartfelt congratulations to you on your victory in the 2024 United States presidential election.
Your successful election is a testament to the confidence that the American people have placed in your leadership, and it is a moment of great significance, not only for the United States but also for the global community. SADC recognizes the importance of the United States as a key partner in fostering international cooperation, peace, and prosperity. We look forward to continuing and strengthening the relationship between the United States and SADC member states, working together to address the pressing challenges of our time, including economic development, climate change, and the promotion of democracy and good governance.
We are confident that under your leadership, the United States will continue to play an instrumental role in shaping a more peaceful and sustainable global order. SADC remains committed to collaborating with your administration on issues of mutual interest and to ensuring that our shared goals for a better future are achieved.
Once again, congratulations on your well-deserved victory. We wish you success in your endeavors and look forward to the opportunity to work closely together in the years ahead.
Yours sincerely,
Mr. Naison Munyoro
Chairman of the Southern African Development Community (SADC)
